caption: I enjoy dining at Red's once a year during my yearly visits to Las Vegas.  The staff and food are always fantastic.  5 stars for sure.  For the record, for 5 straight years it has been great, no exceptions.  The bad reviews are sour people - do not believe these evil people.  Red's is the best!
It was closed
The Hotel are cleaned & in compliance with CDC guidelines.
An average experience. Not much to talk about other than to be able to grab sushi in or on your way to where you’re headed in Vegas. Can almost reach a slot machine from the table, so there’s that.

It was ok but nothing really special. They do have some good happy hour appetizer specials. However the Garlic Chicken Karage was seriously dry so I didn't eat much of it. The bartender was friendly but somewhat forgetful I had to repeat myself several times. I don't care for sake but he did give me a little bit to taste.

Horrible! If I could give them no stars I would.  Don’t waste your time or money. Ramen was disgusting, salad was doused in a heavy ginger mayonnaise dressing and sushi was mediocre and topped with an inedible crab mush that looked like a ball of vomit. Waiter was apathetic at best bordering on rude. Would not recommend and will certainly never eat here again.

The staff was friendly & attentive! The food came out very fast and appeared to be microwaved due to the  hot food temperature. The general tso’s chicken was not good and the magnolia beef had more onions than beef. Very disappointed considering the prices of these meals. Pass on this restaurant!
Great sushi. Great chefs. Bartender Pancho was excellent with great experience great drinks and a excellent personality.
this is the worst asian food I've had in my life.

I sent my friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I visit this place often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are fantastic and the team is welcoming and cooperative. Whenever we eat in this place we have a cheerful evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.

Had to go back. People watch, enjoy the sushi chefs make beautiful sushi rolls, hand rolls and other creations. We tried a couple of the specialty rolls, green tea and kiran beer. Sushi is tasty. I will say the wasabi was not as good as I remembered.  It was gritty, didn't have a kill at all and had a bit of a sweet flavor. But, we didn't really need it with the spicy roll we ordered and the other, we used the soy sauce.
Delicious food at a very reasonable price. I really enjoyed the General Tso's Chicken.
Best sushi in Vegas

Save your time and money! The sushi "chefs" are absolutely disgusting! They touch raw food (tuna) from one container (not fresh) and go into another cooked food (tempura) container without cleaning their hands. Food contamination is bad here. Very unsanitary and the food has a bad smell and taste. Our waitress was a very great person she was not a reflection of this place. Enter at your own risk!
Great & fresh sushi!
Good food

Red Sushi is a pretty good sushi place in Vegas. Service was very fast and manager came by to ask if everything was okay. Food was fresh and well-presented. Price was reasonable for the portions that you received. I saw several reviews that said the price was too high but maybe they're used to eating gas station sushi. Good experience overall and we'll eat there again next time in Vegas
Very slow service. Rude customer service. Food was really weird. Not a great experience. For how expensive it is, it wasn't worth it
I see the reviews, but tonight...
Bee waiting for a half an hour now, everyone around us already ate and left. Tried to get manager's attention, he just walked away. Won't be back

We enjoyed our dinner at RED sushi. The manager was able to accomodate GF needs and they seemed responsive to my concerns. We shared the lettuce wraps and each had sushi. Everything was yummy. It is high priced but expected in the area.
Delicious and fresh!!
I very much enjoyed my time here. Food was great, service as well
Good food! A little pricey for what you get but still good. I went here twice during my stay at the Golden Nugget.
Good happy hour specials! The softshell crab roll was very good!
We had the best waitress. She was so sweet and we had amazing sushi. The chef made us a chef’s special that was absolutely amazing!!
Very cool place to enjoy some good sushi
Sushi was terrible. Way over priced for what you get.
Not very good food and wayyyy over priced. Also did not like that the Philly roll has smoked salmon. It didn't have a description of course so I was expecting the usual Philly roll with raw salmon.
Poor quality food, but nice service.

Our favorite sushi spot in DTLV. We have eaten here several times throughout our stay at the Golden Nugget. The food is fresh and comforting. But the real shout out goes to our server whom we have had every visit! Yu Ling!! She’s so nice and she really made our visit enjoyable.
Delicious. Don't believe negative reviews.

Sushi rolls are really small !! And don’t get any soup with noddles it not good.   Wish I would have readed  this before we ate there.  We will not eat there again  we are a Asian family food there was not good
Delicious...
Sushi tastes like grocery store sushi
Good food love sushi
Amazing.
Wasn't good. Was starving on Freemont St and thought I'd try it. Was expensive and some of the sushi was too chewy for my liking.
Firecracker roll and shrimp tempura roll were amazing
Over rated
Worst sushi ever. Was not impressed for the price. It was old salmon.  The salmon was brown. I had one piece and about puked it up.
Delicious! And amazing happy hour pricing!
Excellent sushi with a great happy hour!

Sorry to say this place was very subpar. Living on the west coast I'm very familiar with good fresh sushi and this was quite disappointing. The staff was friendly and attentive and the chefs were friendly. The issue for me was the quality of the ingredients. Also it was (to me) very overpriced. Typically I pay between 1.75 and 2 bucks for a piece of tuna nigiri. Here it was 10 bucks for 2 tiny pieces. Next the nigiri tasted like chemicals and the fried rice was flat and bland. Sorry for the review but I think the quality of ingredients was subpar.
The manager was so nice and so was the staff. The service and food were amazing. Red sushi is a hidden jewel downtown! Loved the sushi, cocktails and the entrees!
Great service fresh taste worth price
The service was very slow. We only ordered three rolls and had to ask for our waitress because we didn’t see her for almost 20 minutes. Sushi was good. Wouldn’t pay the price for the service again.

Ok if you don't mind not eating together. Food came out at different times. Three of us had finished our mains 10 minutes before the other two received theirs.. Waitress wasn't happy that I wouldn't tip. What did she expect..we should of received a refund as we would expect if it happened back home
Best place I've ever had sushi! The guy making it was super friendly as well as waitresses! Loved it and would definitely go back
Great sushi and great service and great prices too

To be quite fair I went there and end up leaving paying no bill. The manager was very professional, nice and understanding. Unfortunately it was definitely not a great dining experience when it came to the taste of the food. I love sushi but it didn’t taste right to myself.
Great sushi. Good hot food too. Friendly and helpful staff.  Just a little pricey
I’m a Vegas local and this was my first time to Red Sushi. Off the charts presentation for the catapillar roll. Great sake. Good service. Overall food was delicious and I will definitely be back.

Didn’t like the taste of the food plus I found a little piece of hair in my plat but I was lucky and did not put food in it lol. The environment is not for a sushi restaurant at all. Not recommended.  Thanks for reading!
Tempora roll is excelent!
Awesome food......CJ is awesome!!! A must try!!
Great sushi! Alfonso was excellent server and bar tender!

Paid to much for the little food that was given to us. We ordered 2 large edename and they combined them. When i asked where was my other ordered she told me they are not making   any more and she can separate my order into two containers. That was awful. I also ordered the large shrimp tempaura and i got two small shrimp. 30.00 for that. I will never go back there again.

Bad experience,  they charged us way to much for what we got.  They added chili over our edaname and we did not want it like that they wouldn't change it for us.  They charged us for 2 large orders and gave us 1 and said they weren't gonna make more.  She wanted to separate our 1 large order into 2. Even our shrimp tempra roll was only four pieces  it should of been 8. I would never go back nor recommend any one there.

It gets as high as a one-star only because I can't make it lower than one star. I had the gyoza, tiger roll and a spicy tuna roll. All of it was hands down the worst I've ever eaten. I could not choke down all of what I ordered. I've had better sushi from a grocery store. Extremely disappointing.
My family enjoyed Red Sushi. The seared Ahi was very good and was our pick. Cool setting and scenery.

My advice is:   Do not waste your money in this place.  Awful service and awful sushi.  My noodles from my ramen soup wasn’t cooked.   They told me “that is normal”.  I told them “this is not my first time eating ramen soup”.  Avoid this place!
Decent sushi  with great service at the sushi bar.

Should've listened to the reviews. Sushi was gross! Not worth the price. The types are simple and flavor is bland. Sushi was poorly made, stuck to the plate, inside had a mushy texture. "Chef" rushed making the order and then checked his phone. Please do this a favor and don't eat here. Should be ashamed advertising this place.

Ew. So disappointing. Do. Not. Spend. Your. Money. Here. There’s only a dozen other sushi places you can go with better rolls, fresher fish, better customer service, etc.  If you’re really hungry and you’re at this location, you’re better off getting the wings at the hotel pool.

Honestly came here for happy hour but, this quality of food is embarrassing for the pricing. I stuck to the happy menu and was hugely disappointed. The sake bomb is a joke. $4 and you get a shot and a sip of beer. The karage chicken is cover with some sweet teriyaki like sauce that makes it too sweet and soggy. ( I've never had soggy karage) that's not karage lol. I guess they were going for some asaian fusion type of deal but..... And I'm not sure how you can get a crunch roll wrong but they managed to do that as well. It's literally a piece of shrimp with rice and no avocado or cucumber. They they put too much eel sauce to makes it too sweet.  I don't know who's running the show but I suggest a total menu over haul.
Worst dragon roll ever dont waste ur time ....

The sushi here is very basic and it is tasty, but I expected much bigger portions, as compared to other sushi restaurants for the price. The service was good and the waitress was friendly. The best part was the sake bombs, that are super cheap during happy hour.
Happy hour is great
Great atmosphere and food. Very tasty.
Awesome service great cuts... Brian we will be back brotha

Dont get any of the noodle soups, it is just ramen with bad pork.   the sushi is being rationed out too so dont expect too much sushi either. Dont ecpect to get big portions and dont expect quality.  This mediocrity would never fly in Dallas.  The service was good which is the only redeeming factor.
Food is excellent. They do a good job with service and presentation. Priced very well compared to what I've had in Vegas!

Food was awesome., But however my waitress was uncool. I spent $130 on our dinner and drinks. Didn't even finish tipping her yet but put $4 to round up my balance. She went ahead and start discussing my tip with her co-workers Infront of me. Rude. I didn't even wanted to tip her after. However my friend left her over $10 in tip. I even turned around and told the Asian lady that was in cool.

Worst sushi restaurant ever my friend has an impairment and they took as being drunk... rude server and manager worst customer service ever I will never ever go back I've been going there for 10 years and management is horrible and very disrespectful to people with special abilities. I will never go back and there sushi is dry and gross!!!
The taste is very original. If you're a sushi lover, you will love it.
Fresh and tasty sushi. However, prices are very expensive. I was also surprised that they didn't have one of the basic menu items (tamago) the night I went.
This place was so fresh and yummy!
Great food with ok service. The firecracker roll was super tasty.

Terrible service.  Good food.  Good drinks.  Met by Christine who did not seem interested in serving.  Our order was taken by the manager - who was busting his butt keeping the place going.  Betty ended up taking over and basicaly just delivered the food.  The only person (beside the manager) doing well was Alba (bussing and water service).  Christine was real interested when iy was time to pay the bill....sorry honey...10secs of smiling dont get u a good tip.  Take your business elsewhere.
The food was good but the prices were sky high and the proportions were very small. Waitress was very helpful, looking to spend money well you can come I guess.
Great Sushi Good Prices Go eat it!
Good sushi
the waitress was very rude, i was waiting for her long time, and she come ask me if i want eat or not.
Good sushi. Portions are pretty big.

Sat at the bar and ordered. The bartender was awesome! Very friendly and knowledgeable. The sushi was very good. I did not like the salad, I couldn't eat more than two bites of it, but everything else was absolutely delicious! A little high priced, but not a bad value, especially in a casino.
